---
import LessonLayout from '../../layouts/LessonLayout.astro';
---
<LessonLayout
  title="Sensors & Responses"
  track="young-builders"
  week={6}
  phase="Phase 2: Reachy Basics"
  duration="60 min"
  emoji="🎯"
  objective="Read from Reachy's sensors and write reactive code"
>
  <section class="lesson-section mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-builder-700 mb-3">🎯 Learning Objective</h2>
    <p class="bg-builder-50 border-l-4 border-builder-400 p-4 rounded-r-xl text-gray-700">
      You will build a "sense → decide → act" loop using simulated sensor data, creating a robot that reacts to its environment.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="lesson-section mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-3">📋 Activity Steps</h2>
    <div class="space-y-4">
      <div class="flex gap-4 items-start">
        <span class="w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-builder-500 text-white font-bold flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">1</span>
        <div><h3 class="font-bold">Design a Reaction System (15 min)</h3><p class="text-gray-600">On paper: create a table. Column 1: sensor reading. Column 2: what should Reachy do? Fill in at least 6 rows.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="flex gap-4 items-start">
        <span class="w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-builder-500 text-white font-bold flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">2</span>
        <div><h3 class="font-bold">Implement the Loop (30 min)</h3><p class="text-gray-600">Code the sense→decide→act loop. Test it with different simulated inputs. Add at least 2 new reactions beyond the starter code.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="flex gap-4 items-start">
        <span class="w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-builder-500 text-white font-bold flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">3</span>
        <div><h3 class="font-bold">State Machine (15 min)</h3><p class="text-gray-600">What if Reachy has MODES? Happy mode vs Tired mode. In happy mode it reacts enthusiastically; in tired mode, minimally. Implement 2 modes.</p></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="lesson-section mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-3">💻 Code Snippet</h2>
    <pre is:raw class="bg-gray-900 text-green-300 rounded-xl p-5 overflow-x-auto text-sm leading-relaxed"><code># reactive_robot.py — Week 6: Young Builders
import random
import time

class ReachyMock:
    def say(self, msg): print(f"🔊 {msg}"); time.sleep(0.5)
    def wave(self): print("👋 *waves*"); time.sleep(0.5)
    def set_emotion(self, e): print(f"😊 *{e} face*"); time.sleep(0.3)
    def move_head(self, yaw=0): print(f"👀 Head yaw {yaw}°"); time.sleep(0.3)

try:
    from reachy_mini import ReachyMini
    robot = ReachyMini()
except Exception:
    robot = ReachyMock()

def simulate_environment():
    """Generate a random sensor reading."""
    events = [
        {"type": "person_detected", "distance": random.randint(50, 200)},
        {"type": "loud_sound", "level": random.randint(70, 100)},
        {"type": "touch", "location": random.choice(["head", "arm"])},
        {"type": "dark", "light_level": random.randint(0, 30)},
        {"type": "idle", "duration": random.randint(1, 10)},
    ]
    return random.choice(events)

def react(robot, event, mode="happy"):
    """React to an environment event based on current mode."""
    etype = event["type"]
    print(f"\n📡 Sensor: {event}")

    if mode == "tired":
        robot.set_emotion("sleepy")
        robot.say("Zzz... noted.")
        return

    # Happy mode reactions
    if etype == "person_detected":
        robot.set_emotion("happy")
        robot.wave()
        robot.say(f"Hello! You're {event['distance']}cm away!")
    elif etype == "loud_sound":
        robot.set_emotion("surprised")
        robot.say("Whoa, that was loud!")
    elif etype == "touch":
        robot.set_emotion("happy")
        robot.say(f"You touched my {event['location']}! That tickles!")
    elif etype == "dark":
        robot.set_emotion("curious")
        robot.say("It's getting dark. Should I turn on a light?")
    else:
        robot.set_emotion("neutral")

# Run the reactive loop
print("🤖 Starting reactive robot (5 events)\n")
mode = "happy"  # Try changing to "tired"!

for i in range(5):
    event = simulate_environment()
    react(robot, event, mode=mode)
    time.sleep(0.5)</code></pre>
  </section>

  <section class="lesson-section mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-3">💬 Reflection Questions</h2>
    <div class="space-y-3">
      <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-xl p-4"><p class="font-semibold text-blue-800">💭 What's the difference between a reactive robot and a programmed routine?</p></div>
      <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-xl p-4"><p class="font-semibold text-blue-800">💭 What are the risks of a robot reacting without thinking?</p></div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="lesson-section mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-3">👪 Parent Tips</h2>
    <div class="bg-purple-50 border border-purple-200 rounded-xl p-5 text-gray-700">
      <p>💡 The "state machine" (modes) concept is used in everything from traffic lights to video game AI. Your child is learning a core CS pattern!</p>
    </div>
  </section>
</LessonLayout>
